This paper deals with image superresolution using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image synthesis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of novel loss functions tailored for local orientations, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with image processing and manipulation, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
